Avocado Hummus for a little twist on the classic. Thank you @sweetlulu330 for the recipe!

1 avocado
1 can of chickpeas, drained and rinsed
3 tbs lemon juice
2 tbs tahini
1 garlic clove
Salt and pepper
1/4 cup water
Parsley, olive oil and zaatar for garnish 

Put everything in a food processor except the water and garnishes. Blend until well combined. Scrape the sides if needed. Run it again and slowly add water until it gets nice and creamy. Taste test and adjust to your liking. Garnish with extra chickpeas, parsley, zaatar and olive oil and serve with your favorite bread. 

#hummus #avocado #middleeasternfood @lebanese_delicious_dishes #healthy healthyrecipe #vegan

Kafta bil Suniyeh. Literal translation - Kafta in a tray. There are lots of ways to make Kafta and one of them happens to be… IN A TRAY! 🤣 baked to perfection with potatoes, onions and tomatoes. 

2-3 lbs Kafta meat 
3 Idaho potatoes, peeled and sliced 1/4in
1 medium onion, sliced 
2-3 tomatoes, sliced 1/4in

Sauce:
2 tbs Olive oil 
1/4 cup diced onions
2 garlic cloves, minced
1/4 cup diced tomatoes
3 tbs chopped cilantro 
1 tbs tomato paste
3 cups of water
Salt and pepper 

Pre heat oven to 400F. Prep potatoes, onions and tomatoes. Fry potatoes only half way to get them softened. This will ensure they are fully cooked at the end. 

In a 9x13 baking dish, press Kafta meat evenly (about 1/2in thick) and place in the oven for about 15 min or until it shrinks and moisture is released. (I made 1.5 trays because the Kafta will shrink so you’ll be able to put them all in one tray once it’s cooked). While it bakes, make your sauce by heating oil in a small pot and adding onions to cook for 5 min. Add garlic, tomatoes, cilantro and tomato paste and mix for 1 min. Add water and bring to a boil for 2 min then set aside. Drain the excess water from the Kafta. Cut into squares. Layer onions potatoes and tomatoes on top of Kafta and pour sauce on top of kafta. Add salt and pepper. Return to the oven to bake for 30 min. Serve with vermicelli rice and enjoy!

#kafta #kaftabilsanieh #middleeastern #middleeasternfood @lebanese_delicious_dishes

Garlic Cilantro Baked Chicken Leg and Thighs 

Easily one of my favorite recipes. So easy, and everything goes in one tray. What more could you ask for???

6 chicken leg and thighs
3 garlic cloves, minced
1/4 cup cilantro, chopped
Juice of 2 small or 1 large lemon
1/4 cup olive oil
1 tbs paprika
Salt and pepper 
1/2 cup water
Mini potatoes, cut in half
1 carrot, peeled and sliced

Pre heat oven to 400F. Prep chicken by cleaning it in a mixture of water and a splash of vinegar. Pat dry and place on a baking tray. Season with salt and pepper. Place in the oven for 15 min to allow the moisture to release. Drain access moisture. Add potatoes and carrots. Mix all remaining ingredients for the sauce and pour evenly over chicken. Return to the oven to bake for another 30 min or until potatoes and carrots are tender. Serve hot.

Perfect hash browns for that Sunday morning, Christmas breakfast. 

4 Idaho potatoes, peeled, shredded on the large holes
Onion powder
Garlic powder
Salt and pepper
Oil and butter 

Peel your potatoes and shred them into a bowl. Squeeze as much of the moisture out of the potatoes as you can and place the shredded potatoes in a separate bowl. Season with a little bit of onion and garlic powder. Heat a heavy bottom pan or a cast iron pan with a tablespoon of oil and butter. Add your potatoes to the pan and one even later and let it cook on medium heat for about six minutes. Once the bottom has browned, cut into halves or quarters, and flip to cook on the other side add a little bit more butter along the edges and let it cook until it’s crispy on the bottom, season with some salt and pepper and you’re done!

Fluffy Pancakes. So fluffy, you’re going to wish you could take a nap on them after you lick the plate clean. 

2 cups all-purpose Flour
4 Tbsp Sugar, I used coconut 
4 tsp Baking Powder
1/4 tsp Baking Soda
1/2 tsp Salt
1 3/4 cups Milk
4 Tbsp unsalted Butter, melted
2 tsp Vanilla Extract
1 Egg
1/2 cup fresh blueberries 

Mix all dry ingredients in a bowl. Make a well in the center and add the remaining wet ingredients. Mix well until fully incorporated. Add blueberries and food in. Heat a skillet or griddle with some oil or butter over medium heat and pour 1/4 - 1/3 cup to form each pancake. Makes about 8 pancakes. 

#pancakes #fluffy #fluffypancakes

2 ingredient no bake cookies. A delicious and easy mid-day snack for you and the baby!

1/2 cup pitted dates
1/2 cup peanut butter

Remove pits from dates. Of they are very dry, rehydrate in some warm water for 5-10 min. Otherwise you can skip this step. Add the dates with peanut butter to a food processor and run until well combined. Form into cookie and enjoy right away or allow them to sit in the fridge for an hour or so.

Narnumru- this one is new to me but I figure I give it a go.

Sautéed onion and pomegranate seeds with eggs. Although the pomegranate flavor didn’t come through, I enjoyed the texture it gave the dish along with the cooked shallots. Repeat dish? Eh, probably not but glad I learned something new in the kitchen 👍🏽

1 tbs butter
1 small shallot, diced 
1/4 cup pomegranate seeds
2-3 eggs

melt butter in a pan and sauté your shallots or onion for about 3 to 5 minutes. Add the pomegranate seeds and allow to cook for an additional minute. Make a few wells and add your egg and cover until cooked to your liking. Season with salt and pepper, and serve with some toasted bread.

Fresh Kale with Roasted Beets and Chickpeas, Fried Halloumi, and a delicious Lemon Vinaigrette

Kale, stems removed, chopped
4 beets, peeled, cubed
1 can of chickpeas, drained and rinsed
Halloumi cheese or you can simply used crumbled feta
Sunflower seeds
Pecans
Dried Cranberries

Dressing - Mix all ingredients for the dressing in a jar.

Add peeled and cubed beets along with rinsed ch ok peas to a baking sheet lined with parchment or foil. Add seasonings of your liking (I essentially used a taco mix). Assemble salad with all the goods and add your dressing.

Lahme w riz (beef and rice) topped with chicken and chicken noodle soup. 

2 middle Eastern dishes using two whole chickens, boiled in one pot.

let’s just say you won’t be cooking for at least four days after you make this recipe.

2 whole chickens plus spices for homemade broth (cinnamon sticks, cardamom pods, black, peppercorn, cloves, salt)
1/4 cup pine nuts, toasted
1/4 cup almonds, toasted
2 lbs ground beef
7 spice, cinnamon, salt and pepper
1/2 large onion, diced
2 cups basmati rice, soaked and drained
Cooked green peas(optional)

Soup
3 large carrots, peeled and diced 
1/2 cup soaked Egyptian rice
1/2 cup vermicelli noodles
1/4 cup parsley, chopped
Chicken and broth

begin by boiling two whole chickens in a large pot with spices you would use to make your own broth such as cinnamon sticks, cardamom, peppercorns, and cloves. Toast, your pinenuts and almonds in a pan with a little oil making sure not to burn. Set aside. In a separate pan, browned your beef and add your seven spice and cinnamon and salt and pepper. To a pot cook your diced onion, and some oil until dark and almost burnt. Add half of your beef mixture and your basmati rice. Give it a mix and then add enough chicken broth to cook your rice, about 4 cups. Once the rice is cooked through, played it on a large dish, topped with some cooked peas, the remainder of your ground beef, toasted nuts, and meat from one chicken. 

For the soup, use the same broth you made, ensuring it is strained from all of the spices, add your diced carrots, and bring to a boil. Add your Gyptian rice and vermicelli noodles. Cook until rice is soft and add fresh parsley and the rest of your chicken. Season with salt to your liking.

#middleeasternfood #riz #lahme #chicken #chickennoodlesoup

Pesto. Pasta. Perfection. 

Pesto recipe

2 cups basil leaves
1 garlic clove
1/3 cup grated Parmesan cheese
1/3 cup pine nuts or nut of choice
Salt and pepper
1/2 cup olive oil

Blend all dry ingredients in a food processor. Once well combined, slowly add olive oil until well combined. Boil some pasta making sure to reserve 1/3 cup pasta water. In a bowl, add pesto, pasta water and mix. Toss in drained noodles and mix until well coated.  Too with more grated Parmesan cheese.

Instant pot Chuck Roast. Super tender, packed with flavor and will feed the family and the neighbors 🤣
In order of use:
Olive oil
3-4 lbs chuck roast (I used 2 lbs and froze the rest)
Seasonings: salt, pepper, chili powder, onion powder, garlic powder, paprika 
1 onion, diced
4 whole garlic cloves, peeled and smashed
2 cups broth
2 tbs balsamic vinegar
2 tbs Worcestershire sauce
2 tbs tomato paste
2-3 medium carrots, peeled and sliced thick 
About 12 baby potatoes, sliced in half 

Slice chuck roast into 1.5-2in pieces. Season both sides generously. Set instant pot to sauté mode. Add oil and sear both sides for 4 min on each side. You may need to do this is batches. Remove beef and set aside. Add diced onions and garlic to pot. Sauté for 5 min. Add broth, balsamic, Worcestershire and tomato paste. Mix and add beef back to the pot. Cover and set to pressure cook. Set for 1 hour. In the meantime, prep your veggies and potatoes. Once timer goes off, allow to release pressure naturally. Remove beef and add potatoes and carrots. Pressure cook for 3 min. Shred beef in a tray and add potatoes and carrots on the side when done. Cover with juices. Make a gravy with the sauce if you like. 

#instantpotrecipes #instantpot #potroast #tenderbeef @instantpotofficial

Cashew Chicken with Cilantro Rice. Tip: Add some diced pineapple at the end. Trust me. ITS DROP DEAD DELICIOUS!

Cooking oil
1.5 lbs chicken breast, flattened and cubed
2 small onions, diced
1 garlic clove, minced
Veggies of your choosing: 1 bell pepper, diced. mushrooms, sliced. or green beans 
1 cup cashews, toasted

Sauce
1/2 cup soy
2 tbs apple cider vinegar or rice vinegar
1/2 tbs sesame oil
1 tbs honey 
2 tbs sweet chili sauce
1 tbs corn starch
2 garlic cloves, chopped
1/2 cup water

Toast raw cashews for 5 min or until lightly browned.
Don’t burn them, they will continue to cook as they cool.
Mix all ingredients for the sauce in a bowl and set aside.
Flatten chicken breast with a mallet and cut into 1 in squares. In a large pan with some cooking oil, brown chicken. Season with salt and pepper. Once browned, transfer to a bowl and set aside. In the same pan heat 1 tbs cooking oil and cook onions and garlic for 1 min. Then add remaining veggies and cook for 5 min mixing frequently. Transfer chicken back to the pan along with the cashews. Pour in sauce and mix well. Bring to a simmer and allow sauce to thicken, mixing frequently. Serve with rice and garnish with sesame seeds.

#cashewchicken #recipes #chickenrecipes

Slow Cooker Chicken Chili all done in the instant pot. 
(Pressure cooking method also below)

1.5 lbs chicken breast
1 bell pepper, diced
1 medium onion, diced
6 garlic cloves, minced
Jalapeño, diced (optional)
1 can red kidney beans or any beans of your choosing, drained and rinsed 
Seasonings if your liking. I used: paprika, garlic and onion powder, cumin, oregano, chili powder salt and pepper
2-3 cups chicken or vegetable broth
1 can full fat coconut milk, or 1.5 cups milk
1 can or 1 cup of drained corn
1 lime, juiced 

Garnishes:
Avocado
Jalapeño
Cilantro
Cheese
Tortilla chips

In a slow cooker (I used my instant pot) add first 8 ingredients and mix. Set slow cooker to 6 hours on low or 3 hours on high. When done, remove chicken and shred. Transfer back to the pot and add milk, corn and lime. Set instant pot to sauté for 10 min or slow cook on high for an additional 10-20 min. Adjust taste to your liking. Serve hot with your favorite garnishes. 

Attentively, you can pressure cook by adding chicken, seasoning and broth to the pot and pressure cook for 10 min allowing the pressure to release naturally. Remove chicken to shred. Then add chicken and all remaining ingredients back to the pot for 3 min of pressure cooking allowing the pressure to release naturally. Serve with garnishes. 

#instantpot #instantpotrecipes @instantpotofficial #chickenchili #soup #soupseason #soupszn

Lasagna. 

16 oz box Lasagna Pasta, cooked
11/2 cups Mozzarella cheese, shredded for topping 
1/2 cup Parmesan cheese, grated or shredded for topping
Fresh parsley for garnish

Meat Sauce: 
2 Ibs ground beef
2 medium onions, diced
8 small garlic cloves, minced
28oz can crushed tomatoes
(2)15oz cans tomato sauce
1 tbs of each: dried basil, dried oregano, Italian seasoning
3 tsp salt, 1 tsp black pepper

Ricotta filling
(2) 15 oz jars Ricotta cheese
1 large eggs
2 cups shredded mozzarella cheese
1/4 cup fresh chopped parsley
1 tsp salt + 1/4 tsp black pepper

Boil noodles according to packaging. I prefer them taken out 2 min before suggested cooking time as it will cook in the oven later. Drain and rinse under cold water and set aside. 

In a large, deep pan over medium heat, add beef, onions, and garlic. If using lean meat, add 1-2 tsp oil. Otherwise, no need for oil. Cook while mixing for 10-12 min. 

Next, add crushed tomatoes, tomato sauce, dried basil, dried oregano, Italian seasoning, salt and black pepper. Cook 10 mins, covered to prevent splashing. 

Make ricotta filling by mixing all ricotta ingredients very well in a bowl. 

Spray inside of deep 9x13 baking dish with nonstick spray.
Spread 1 cup of meat sauce to bottom of dish, cover with 4 cooked lasagna sheets. Spread 2 cups meat sauce on pasta then spread 1/3 portion of ricotta mixture on top. Add another layer of lasagna sheets, and repeat… (meat sauce, ricotta, pasta, meat sauce, ricotta, pasta)

Sprinkle 1 1/2 cup mozzarella cheese and 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese on top. 

Pre heat oven to 375F. Spray the inside of foil with nonstick spray and cover lasagna. Bake for 45 minutes. Remove foil. Bake another
15 minutes. Then broil on high for 3 mins or until golden brown on top. Cool for 15 mins before cutting. Garnish with parsley and enjoy!

Chicken and Broccoli Stir Fry

When Monday comes around, we need meals like this to come together in just 30 minutes. Am I right?

1.5 lbs chicken breast, cubed
4 cups Broccoli florets
1 onion, sliced
4-6oz mushrooms, sliced
2 garlic cloves, minced
Pinch of black pepper
Toasted sesame seeds

Sauce:
1 and 1/4 cup chicken broth, or veggie or water
1/4 cup soy sauce
1 tbs sesame oil
1 garlic clove, minced
2 tbs brown sugar or honey
1 tbs corn starch 

Mix everything for the sauce in a bowl. Set aside. In a large pan, heat some oil and add cubed chicken. Season with black pepper. Allow to brown on one side before mixing. When completely browned, remove from the pan and set aside. Add more oil to the pan and add your broccoli, mushrooms, onions and garlic. Mix constantly for 5 min or until broccoli is tender. Add chicken back to the pan. Give your sauce another mix to make sure it hasn’t settled and pour into the pan. Mix everything to fully coat in the sauce. Lower heat to a simmer and gently mix. Allow sauce to thicken. Add 1 tsp of toasted sesame seeds and mix. Serve with cooked rice and garnish with more sesame seeds.

Is it RIZ or RUZ? Aka rice. 

Ramadan Food Chronicles with @_simplyss_ 

Episode 1: Bazella - beef and green pea tomato based stew served with rice. 

1 pound filet or ribeye meat 
2 tbsp olive oil 
1 bunch cilantro, chopped
8-10 garlic cloves, minced 
1 onion, chopped
4 cups water
2/3 of 6oz can of tomato paste 
1 bag peas 12 oz 
1 bag carrots 12oz 
2 tsp salt and pepper 
Sprinkle of dried cilantro

Heat a pot over medium heat. Add beef and brown for 7 min while mixing. The water from the beef will release. Use paper towel to soak it all out. Once dried out, add olive oil and sauté while mixing for 3-5 min. Add cilantro, garlic and onion. Sauté for 3 more minutes while mixing. Add water and tomato paste and stir. Bring to a boil then add peas and carrots, salt and pepper and dried cilantro. Mix and bring to a simmer. Cover for 7-10 min to allow all the flavors to come together. Serve with middle eastern rice (see rice recipe below

1 cup khalo Ben rice, soaked in warm water for 10 min
1/2 cup vermicelli noodles
1 tbs butter + 1 tbs olive oil
Water
Pinch of salt

In a deep pan or pot, add oil and butter over medium heat. Once butter has melted, add vermicelli noodles. Mix constantly to brown. Ensure you don’t burn it. Add drained rice and mix. Add water just enough to cover the top by 1/4in. Add a pinch of salt and mix. Cover over low heat until all the water is absorbed. Fluff with a fork. Serve with Bazella. 

#ramadan #ramadankareem #ramadanmubarak #ramadanrecipes #ramadan2023 #bazella

Roasted Mexican Street Corn (Elote) Dip makes you dance funny. You’ll see what I mean when you try it.

4 heads of fresh corn, cut off the cob or 2 cans of drained corn
2 tbs fresh cilantro, chopped
Juice of a lime wedge
4 oz cream cheese
1/4 cup mayo
Cotija cheese (optional)
1 tbs Mexican seasoning 
Mexican blend shredded cheese

In an oven safe pan, roast corn over medium high heat with some oil. Once it starts to brown slightly, remove pan from heat and allow to cook for a couple minutes. While it’s still warm, add cilantro, lime juice, cream cheese, mayo, cotija if using, and seasoning. Mix well and smooth it out to one even layer. Too with shredded cheese and place in the oven to broil on high for a few minutes until cheese starts to brown slightly. Serve with tortilla chips.

Ramadan Food Chronicles, recipe #2: Sfouf, aka Turmeric Cake, aka yellow cake baked with Samira and Shereen Saad from @_simplyss_ 

Ramadan isn’t Ramadan without the fluffiest yellow cake and this fool proof recipe comes together so quickly and easily with just 5 min of prep, 30min of baking, 0.2 seconds to devour. 

This recipe is allergen free. Some recipes call for tahini (sesame paste) but not this one!!

Dry Ingredients:
2.5 cups flour
2.5 cups sugar
0.5 cups semolina 
1 tbsp baking powder
1 tbsp turmeric 

Wet ingredients:
2 cups vitamin D milk
1 cup corn oil

🌙 Preheat oven to 350 degrees
🌙 Mix all dry ingredients together making sure to remove any clumps. Don’t do what @oh_my_foodness did!
🌙 Add in wet ingredients and mix with a mixer until well combined 
🌙 Spray a 9x13 pan with Pam and pour cake mix into pan. 
🌙Bake approximately 30 min or until done (will vary based on oven or size of pan) - as witnessed by the heart shaped pan 🤣

There’s no reason why your baby or toddler can’t eat what the adults are eating (unless of course they have allergies) but these homemade Baked Chicken Nuggets were perfect for the adults and the baby. Nothing beats the taste of fast food nuggets but at least I know this is made with REAL CHICKEN 🤣 these can be fried too, I think. I’ll let you know with the frozen batch. 

1 lb ground chicken
1 tsp salt and pepper and garlic powder
1/4 cup flour
2 eggs, whisked
1/2 cup or so of seasoned bread crumbs

Mix seasonings into chicken. Lay flat on some parchment paper and press with another sheet of paper to one even layer. Cut into nugget shapes. Coat in flour first, then eggs, then bread crumbs. Lay on a baking sheet line with parchment paper and bake at 350F for 20 min or until browned, flipping halfway through baking.

Breakfast with Layla - Strawberry Banana Pancakes

Simple 3 ingredient pancakes for you and your toddler. This one is allergen free (no egg or dairy)

1/2 a banana
3 strawberries 
1/4 cup flour (I used oat flour)
1/4 milk (I used oat milk)
Pinch of cinnamon (optional)
Oil for pan ( I used coconut)

Mash banana and strawberries in a bowl. Then add flour, milk and cinnamon and mix well. Heat a fry pan over medium heat and add oil. Pour batter in and cook for a couple minutes or until bottom is nicely browned then flip to finish the other side. Cut into strips and allow to cool before serving your toddler.

Ramadan Food Chronicles #3
Fattoush Salad 
 
2 heads of Romaine lettuce, chopped
3 small cucumbers, diced
4 Radishes, diced
3 green onions, diced 
2 Roma Tomatoes, diced
1/4 cup fresh Mint, chopped
1 cup of mixed peppers-green, yellow, red, orange, diced

Blueberry Crumble. 

If you hand me a slice of pizza with blueberries on it, I won’t say no to it. My love for blueberries is real. ESPECIALLY when they are baked and they release their sweet delicious juices, just like in this crumble. You can prep and assemble the crumble ahead of time and store it in the fridge until you’re ready to bake. 

For the filling:
5 cups blueberries, frozen or fresh
2 tbs cornstarch
1/2 cup granulated sugar
1/4 tsp. ground cinnamon
1/8 tsp. ground nutmeg
1/2 cup water
2 tsp. fresh lemon juice

For the topping:
2 cups all-purpose flour
2 cups old-fashioned oats
1.5 cups brown sugar
1 tsp ground cinnamon
1 cup butter, melted

Place blueberries in a 9x13 tray. In a bowl, mix all the dry filling ingredients. Add to blueberries and mix. Then add water and lemon and mix. In a separate bowl, mix all the dry topping ingredients well. Then pour in melted butter and mix again until well combined. 

Place topping evenly over berries and into the oven at 350F for 45 min. Serve warm with vanilla ice cream. 

#blueberry #blueberries #blueberrycrumble #blueberrydessert #easydessert

What do you call this?  Namoura? Harisseh? Basbous? Doesn’t matter. Just make this recipe courtesy of my beautiful mother, @sweetlulu330 

Perfect for Ramadan, a traditional Middle-Eastern dessert with a semolina base batter, garnished with nuts, baked then dredged with a rose water simple syrup. 

2 cups semolina (coarse)
1 cup yogurt
3/4 cup sugar
2 tablespoon coconut
1/2 teaspoon baking powder
1/2 teaspoon baking soda
1 tablespoon tahini (for baking tray)
Nuts for garnish

Sugar syrup:
2 cups sugar
1 cup water
1 teaspoon lemon juice
1 teaspoon each Rose water and blossom water
2 tablespoons butter or ghee

For the syrup mix sugar and water over medium heat boil until glossy, boil for 3 minutes then lower heat and add the lemon juice and boil for 2 minutes, turn off heat and add rose water and blossom water, add butter then set aside.
In a round or rectangular baking tray spread a tablespoon of tahini set aside.
In a large bowl add the semolina, coconut, baking powder and soda and mix. Then add sugar to the yogurt and mix well. Pour yogurt to fry ingredients and rub between palms for a sticky texture. If too thick add little more yogurt until you have a smooth consistency. Spread into baking tray, smooth the top with wet hand or spatula. Score the top (don’t cut all the way through yet) to make 2inx2in squares and garnish top with nuts. Preheat oven to 375 F degrees. Bake for about 30 min or until golden brown, broil for a darker top. Take out of oven and immediately pour the warm syrup all over the top and let it soak in as much as you desire. Allow to cool before slicing all the way through. Serve with coffee or tea.

#namoora #namoura #basbousa #basbousacake #ramadan #ramadanrecipes #ramadanrecipe #ramadan2023 #middleeasternfood #middleeasterndessert

Juice of half a large lemon
2 tsp apple cider vinegar 
2 tbs Dijon mustard
1 tbs honey 
1 tbs grated Parmesan or Pecorino Romano
1 tsp garlic powder
Salt and pepper to taste

Stuffed Koussa (zucchini/squash)

I always thought this was one of those intimidating, hard to make middle eastern dishes, but I was totally wrong! A lot easier than I thought. I seriously surprised myself with this one. It was DROP DEAD DELICIOUS. Thanks to @sweetlulu330 for her FaceTiming help. 

10 medium Koussa (Mexican squash/zucchini)
1 lb ground beef
1 medium onion, diced
2 garlic cloves, minced
1 (14oz) can tomato sauce
1 tbs tomato paste
1/2cup of water
Olive oil 
Salt and pepper
1 tbs seven spice, divided 
Toasted pine nuts for garnish.
Middle eastern rice to serve

Begin by trimming the squash. Cut the head and a little bit of the stem (bottom) and discard. Make a cut halfway through the squash making sure not to cut it all the way through. They will be stuffed later. Fry them in oil until soft, about 5 min per side. Remove and allow to cool on a plate lined with paper towel. While it cools, make your meat mixture by adding some olive oil to a pan and sautéing your onion for 5 min. Add beef and mix until beef has browned. Add salt, pepper and 1/2 tbs of seven spice. You can add some toasted pine nuts at this point if you like. Allow to cool. Make your sauce by sautéing garlic in some oil in a small pot then add your tomato sauce, tomato paste and water. Allow paste to dissolve while simmering then add salt, pepper and remainder of the seven spice. Once it has simmered for a few minutes, cover and remove from the heat. 

Begin assembling the koussa by stuffing as much meat inside as you can and place neatly in a deep walled baking tray. Repeat for all the koussa. Pour the sauce all around the koussa making sure the bottom of the tray is completely covered in sauce and not on the koussa. Place in a preheated oven at 375F for 30-40 min or until the sauce has bubbled for about 5-10 min. Remove from the oven and garnish with toasted pine nuts. Serve hot with the sauce and vermicelli rice.

Juice of 1-2 limes 
Salt and pepper, paprika and cumin
Equal parts cornstarch and water (the glue for your tortillas)

Prep all of your veggies. Grill corn until charred. Mash avocados leaving it slightly chunky and mix all veggies together. Add lime and seasonings and mix. Adjust taste to your liking. 

Bring a pot of frying oil to heat. Using cannoli tubes, wrap the corn tortilla around the tube. Brush a mixture of corn starch and water to the end of the tortillas to act as glue to seal it all together. Using metal tongs, gently place it in the hot oil. Hold tongs in the oil for a few seconds to ensure the tortilla doesn’t open up while it fries. Allow to turn golden in color, about 1-2 min. Drain oil and allow to cool. Alternatively, you can use an air fryer until golden brown. 

Fill a piping bag with your guacamole and pipe the guacamole into each end of the tortilla and serve!

My version of Shepard’s pie, hearty meat and veggies sandwiched between two layers of creamy mashed potatoes. Baked to perfection with buttery and crispy crust. 

Meat filling
2 lbs ground beef
3 tbs cooking oil 
2 tbs butter
1 small onion, diced 
1/2 cup frozen peas
1/2 cup frozen corn
1/2 cup bell peppers, diced
1/2 cup carrots, diced
1/2 cup fresh parsley, chopped
2 tbs tomato paste
1 tsp of each: salt, pepper, thyme and garlic seasoning

Potato layer
8 -10 potatoes, boiled, peeled. 
8 tbs butter, divided. 
1 tsp of each: salt, white pepper, garlic seasoning
1/2 cup bread crumbs

Mushroom sauce
1 8oz box mushrooms chopped 
1 small onion chopped
2 tablespoons butter
Thyme, salt and pepper
Dash of white vinegar
2 teaspoons flour 
1/3 water
Mix flour water last together to thicken

In a large pot with water, begin boiling potatoes until soft. In the meantime, heat a large fry pan and brown ground beef. Once browned, add oil and butter and mix. Add all remaining ingredients and mix for another 5 min on low heat. Set aside. 

Allow potatoes to cool, then peel their skin off. Mash it in a bowl or push it through a potato masher. Add 4tbs butter and seasoning and mix well. 

In a 9x13 baking dish, melt 2 tbs butter and spread to coat the inside of the pan. Sprinkle bread crumbs all over to coat the pan. Form one layer of potatoes in the base of your pan spreading it evenly. Add a layer of ground beef on top and then finish with a second layer of potatoes on top. Smooth the surface of the potato. Melt remaining butter and pour evenly on top of the potato’s and sprinkle more bread crumbs. Throw it in the oven at 375F for about 30-40 min or until golden brown on top. 

Make mushroom sauce by sautéing mushrooms and onions in butter in a small pot for 5 min. Then add seasoning and vinegar. In a small bowl, mix flour and water and pour into the pot. Mix while simmering to thicken the sauce. Top your Shepard’s pie with the mushroom sauce and enjoy.
